    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@vvo: No I did not implemented the `template` and `cssClass` because once again we're going back to the same questions :)\n\nI listen to the `checkbox` change event, so allowing for a custom template would raise again all the questions of how we will be able to correctly bind our event if we don't know what the template will compile too.\n\nRegarding the `cssClass`, I'm not even sure the `label` wrapping the `checkbox` will be the final default template. Also, we won't even use this widget in the instant search, so I think we can just keep it like it is for now.\n",
